# Repository Documentation
==============================

1. UserRepository
- Interface: Extends JpaRepository<User, Long>
- Custom Methods:
  - `Optional<User> findByUsername(String username)`: Retrieves a user by their username

2. UrlMappingRepository
- Interface: Extends JpaRepository<UrlMapping, Long>
- Custom Methods:
  - `UrlMapping findByShortUrl(String shortUrl)`: Retrieves a URL mapping by its short URL
  - `List<UrlMapping> findByUser(User user)`: Finds all URL mappings for a specific user

3. ClickEventRepository
- Interface: Extends JpaRepository<ClickEvent, Long>
- Custom Methods:
  - `List<ClickEvent> findByUrlMappingAndClickDateBetween(UrlMapping mapping, LocalDateTime startDate, LocalDateTime endDate)`: 
    - Retrieves click events for a specific URL mapping within a date range
  - `List<ClickEvent> findByUrlMappingInAndClickDateBetween(List<UrlMapping> urlMappings, LocalDateTime startDate, LocalDateTime endDate)`:
    - Retrieves click events for multiple URL mappings within a date range

Common Features:
- All repositories are annotated with @Repository
- All extend JpaRepository with their respective entity types
- Method names follow Spring Data JPA naming conventions
- Query methods are automatically implemented by Spring Data JPA